without issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing testing structure**\\n\\nI’m considering using a class ServiceFactory that implements Factory<String>. I might need to run a test for each call, and think about combining them for efficiency. There's a need for a coverage report for active classes, and I realize tests may cover private static classes without needing odd file names. I've got to verify if test line 462 handles MultiException correctly. It seems like there's a lot to ensure regarding class loading and error management.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading in Native Image**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the class loader in a Native Image app can trigger a ClassNotFoundException, which is good to know. Overriding the ClassLoader seems odd; can I really subclass it? I suppose that should work, but there might be limitations in ClassLoader support. While overriding loadClass seems straightforward, I'm wondering if using the ClassLoader constructor could be an option. I’m also considering whether using ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader as a parent is relevant.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test mapping**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the existing Hk2_locatorTest isn't mapped, which seems like a concern. The rule states there should be a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files, so I'm wondering if it's best not to add anything extra. The user mentioned an active dynamic class, Utilities, so I'll include UtilitiesTest. The existing placeholder remains untouched, but I think the user-code-filter needs to encompass the test package properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DuhY56OCq2DOPStlhlc49t5C|fc_049708e11698621b016a024583859c819f80639ece0f52e5b3", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-locator/2.5.0-b05/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": 